cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on dual-arm anthropomorphic systems and their manipulation capabilities. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end learning-based framework for dual-arm manipulation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the proposed framework involves learning and generalisation capabilities. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) may be relevant as vision-based perception could be used in the dual-arm manipulation tasks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) may also be relevant as the paper discusses the dynamics underlying the system's behaviour.
